Colin hello, I am a furious fan of your channel! I was very impressed with your innovative solutions and developments. I live in the Russian Federation, doing repairs, various household appliances as I have been fond of electronics since childhood. I am also involved in the development and design of various electronic equipment. For yourself, just like you.
I hated cats and everything that was connected with them, but according to the circumstances of fate, I got a cat 8 months ago, very smart and delicate. She eats a lot and accordingly poops a lot. Could you make a device that could recycle the waste products of my beloved cat or at least sort it by separating the filler from them?

At the moment I am developing a project of a power source with parameters from 0 to 50 volts and a protection current from 4 to 20 amperes, with a total power of 1 kilowatt. I can send a printed circuit board control and standby power source. The power unit board is not yet complete. Upon completion of the work, I will send her too.

Please write your answer to my email address: Evgeny_81@bk.ru

snippet.textDisplay:
a request: please, prove/disprove the validity of a certain ou concept; see my research. i cannot do it all. i have funds, but no one to pay. at my oldest videos, i have done some of the math. success would seem to depend, only, on design (and execution). in this area of research, sourcing optimal components is seldom easy. in general, a configuration is determined by whatever, decent (neo-mag) pma is available. i have a pretty good pma. its size and rpm specs require a certain minimum 'scale' of construction, however. resulting in a continuing quest for an optimal prime mover configuration. the design of an efficient large-radius electric motor, a la f&p, seems to have a LOT of potential, here. it should be understood that a motor is Not a pma. a pma is a pma. the design of a diy pma Must follow a few simple rules. 1) there Must be three coils per phase; coils connected in series 2) the number of magnetic poles on the rotor Must be a multiple of four 3) a Generating coil Must be made Correctly. it Should be a brooks coil; consisting of 30 to 35 winds; of 14awg magnet wire/equiv. cheers googletranslate
http://nessengr.com/techdata/brooks/brooks.html
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lTkXciAn488

https://www.fisherpaykeltechnologies.com/products/direct-drive-motors/
